feat(store): typed CRUD repos over chonkers SQL data model

Land the four repos described in docs/DB.md "Repos":
  - matchesRepo: createMatch, getMatch, listMatches, finalizeMatch,
    forfeit, setChain, clearChain, incrementPly. Forfeit records
    forfeit-<color> as the winner field per docs/DB.md so the sim
    broker can dispatch the standard game-over sting + the OPPOSITE
    side's victory voice line.
  - movesRepo: appendMove, getMove, listMovesByMatch (asc by ply),
    latestMoveByMatch (desc by ply, limit 1).
  - aiStatesRepo: upsertDump, getDump. Replace-not-append per the
    composite PK (match_id, profile_key). Buffer-encoded BLOB
    handling so the same code works under better-sqlite3 (Node tier)
    and capacitor-sqlite (runtime).
  - analyticsRepo: upsertAggregate, getAggregate, listByFamily.
    listByFamily uses LIKE with the family-prefix convention from
    docs/DB.md (e.g. "winrate:" matches every win-rate row).

Each repo function takes the drizzle handle as its first argument
so callers compose them inside transactions (drizzle's
db.transaction(fn)). No singleton shortcuts; the broker passes the
handle.

A shared StoreDb type (BaseSQLiteDatabase generic over the schema)
lets every repo accept BOTH the test-tier better-sqlite3 handle from
makeTestDb() AND the runtime sqlite-proxy handle from
src/persistence/sqlite/. Same code path under both backends.

31 new repo CRUD tests against makeTestDb covering happy-path inserts,
update-by-conflict semantics for the upsert repos, FK cascades for
matches→{moves, ai_states}, FK SET NULL for matches→analytics, plus
listByFamily prefix matching and ply-counter monotonicity.

Total: 8 Node-tier test files, 69 tests pass. Browser tier unchanged
(13 kv + 3 bootstrap = 16). Typecheck and lint clean.

